HEADWORD: Buckboard
<hw>Buck"board`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A four-wheeled
vehicle, having a long elastic board or frame resting on the bolsters or
axletrees, and a seat or seats placed transversely upon it; -- called
also <altname>buck wagon</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bucker</ent>⟦br⟧
